DmC Devil May Cry;DmC: Devil May Cry;DmC Devil May Cry;;videos\DmC Devil May Cry (2013).mp4;OK;images\DmC Devil May Cry (2013).webp;;Steam;Ninja Theory;Capcom;24/01/2013;DmC: Devil May Cry is the fifth game in the hack-and-slash third-person action series and the first not largely developed by Capcom. This title is a reimagining of the series, with the same protagonist Dante, but set in an alternate universe. The Dante in this game is very different from before, doing away with the trademark white hair and altering the main character as well as the game's tone with a much more Western influence. The gameplay is still largely identical as Dante engages many opponents with a fast fighting style, stringing together combos and hits in quick succession.;Adventure, Puzzle, Hack and slash/Beat 'em up;;https://video.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_trailers/220440/11820/b7232022da56e7b2bf386dde32418cb601da1aa7/1750481573/hls_264_master.m3u8?t=1447358028;steam_220440;steam_220440;origin_OFB-EAST:109546497;uplay_1702;humble_dmc_devilmaycry_bundle_steam;humble_dmc_devilmaycry_ru_bundle_steam;test_UP0102-NPUB30830_00-DMCDEVILMAYCRY01;humble_dmc_devilmaycry_steam;test_/dmc-devil-may-cry-free-download/;test_dmc-devil-may-cry;playfire_dmc-devil-may-cry;humble_dmc_devilmaycry_ru_steam;humble_dmc_devilmaycry_capcomsummer2022bundle_row_bundle_steam;humble_dmc_devilmaycry_latam_bundle_steam;vision_BLUS30723;generic_51152777159612898;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
Resident Evil Revelations HD;Resident Evil: Revelations 2;Resident Evil Revelations HD;;videos\Resident Evil Revelations HD (2013).mp4;OK;images\Resident Evil Revelations HD (2013).webp;;Steam;Capcom;Capcom, Sony Computer Entertainment;24/02/2015;Resident Evil: Revelations 2 is the retail version of the episodic survival horror series that was originally released as four downloadable episodes. This physical version combines the entire story along with some extras, but not all the available DLC. The PC version did not receive a retail release, but the same content was bundled on Steam. The game comprises four episodes, each of which feature two separate stories. This sequel bears a stronger tone to the concept of survival horror than titles such as Resident Evil 5 and Resident Evil 6. Elements of ammunition management as well as stealth or sneaking come into play in the gameplay.;Adventure, Shooter;;https://video.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_trailers/222480/11635/ad017711ee17f25ea94d68d27d01f59a3468d6fb/1756429580/hls_264_master.m3u8?t=1447357940;steam_222480, steam_287290;steam_287290;psn_CUSA00804_00;steam_steam_287290;psn_CUSA00924_00;psn_CUSA01133_00;psn_CUSA01141_00;psn_CUSA00901_00;psn_CUSA00999_00;test_CUSA00804_00;test_CUSA00924_00;humble_residentevil_revelations2_eu_steam;humble_residentevil_revelations2_row_steam;humble_residentevil_revelations2_steam;humble_residentevil_revelations2_completeseason_eu_bundle_steam;humble_residentevil_revelations2_completeseason_us_asia_bundle_steam;humble_residentevil_revelations2_completeseason_rucis_bundle_steam;origin_be8ed186a38b473044df0d21cb9d87afc81ab956;origin_4d3243ab6e1e2eee273e92146f8740e3f2a386f8899a45c4fa183614065e20df;psn_NPUB31518_00;test_/resident-evil-revelations-2-free-download/;test_resident-evil-revelations-2;playfire_resident-evil-revelations-2;nswitch_010095300212A000;test_287290;generic_51154115821551230;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
Brütal Legend;Brütal Legend;Brütal Legend;;videos\Brütal Legend (2013).mp4;OK;images\Brütal Legend (2013).webp;;Steam;Double Fine Productions;Electronic Arts;26/02/2013;Brütal Legend is an action-adventure that marries visceral action combat with open-world freedom. Set in a universe somewhere between Lord of the Rings and Spinal Tap, it’s a fresh take on the action/driving genre, which in this case is full of imitation cover bands, demons intent on enslaving humanity and Heavy metal tunes. Featuring the talents of comedian, actor and musician, Jack Black as super roadie Eddie Riggs, as well as cameos by some of the biggest names in metal music it's a wild ride in the belly of the beast that is not to be missed by gamers and Metalheads alike.;Adventure, Strategy;;https://video.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_trailers/225260/10608/0fdb25f324c0a1a0a2e5a77a9f44c680ff4c64d5/1750837070/hls_264_master.m3u8?t=1447357433;steam_225260;steam_225260;gog_1207659253;humble_brutallegend;amazon_3ea9dd41-009a-4944-b23b-30d0450d3b90;humble_3ea9dd41-009a-4944-b23b-30d0450d3b90;humble_doublefine_bundle_brutallegendsteam;twitch_3ea9dd41-009a-4944-b23b-30d0450d3b90;xboxone_53026046;3ds_3ea9dd41-009a-4944-b23b-30d0450d3b90;humble_brutallegend_conquercovid19_new_steam;humble_storefront_brutallegend_steam;itch_63058;humble_brutallegend_bundle_steam;test_/brutal-legend-free-download/;test_brutal-legend;playfire_brutal-legend;xboxone_1161889989;test_1c45655b3d232a0f9206bb0aa5f5b2435e689bac;test_4f4c3ea897a8b66020db34460fe6d5b69acc283c;test_5e8755df94356dc1c2836cfb450f858094bd08d2;amazon_43566160-d3df-432b-bd5a-fe9438b588f5;generic_51141995873539057;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
Desktop Dungeons;Desktop Dungeons;Desktop Dungeons;;videos\Desktop Dungeons (2010).mp4;OK;images\Desktop Dungeons (2010).webp;;Steam;QCF Design;QCF Design;18/10/2010;Each step into the unknown heals you and reveals new obstacles as you guide fresh heros to glorious retirement or ignominious death. Master tactical spells, appease ancient gods and get rich through taxidermy in this award-winning quick-play puzzle-roguelike.;Role-playing (RPG), Adventure, Turn-based strategy (TBS), Indie, Puzzle;;https://video.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_trailers/226620/34555/b152dbefd9310d9e4afb19f18902eb97c0b98ca8/1750482345/hls_264_master.m3u8?t=1447373137;steam_226620;steam_226620;gog_1207664703;humble_desktopdungeons;humble_desktopdungeons_steam;test_/desktop-dungeons-free-download/;test_desktop-dungeons;test_226620;generic_51152760432531023;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
Age of Wonders III;Age of Wonders III;Age of Wonders III;;videos\Age of Wonders III (2014).mp4;OK;images\Age of Wonders III (2014).webp;;Steam;Triumph Studios;Triumph Studios;31/03/2014;"Age of Wonders III, like the previous games in the series is a turn-based strategy game set within a high fantasy universe where the player assumes the role of a political-military leader. Gameplay is 4X-based (explore, expand, exploit and exterminate) where players explore the world map, slowly building an empire through colonization, warfare and diplomacy with rival powers. However new to III is the greater addition of role-playing game features, where players must first choose and customize their leader, all options dependant on the player's chosen style of play. There are six available races in the initial release: humans, draconians, high elves, dwarves, orcs, and goblins, all that will determine the race of their empire with each having unique perks and abilities. The leader and empire is further shaped by the choice from skill sets based on traditional RPG classes along with further specializations and skills to select. Each leader class also has access to their own unique units with a distinct visual look based on their corresponding race, each to accommodate their own unique approach to strategy, both in combat and when managing their empire. On release there are six different classes a leader can be. The ""Sorcerer"" class emphasizes the use of magic for enchantments and summoning powerful units. The ""Theocrat"" derives from an organized religion based society including zealots followers and the use of holy spells and warriors. The ""Rogue"" favors less direct approaches to situations, employing stealth, thievery and manipulation aswell as dark magic in diplomacy and warfare. The ""Archdruid"" channels the power of nature, using it to their advantage by being very self-sufficient and being able to call upon wild creatures. The ""Dreadnaught"" leads a steampunk styled society, using large industry, machinery and gunpowder-based units like cannons and tanks. Finally the ""Warlord"" specializes in direct conflict and combat tactics, utilizing effective non-magic based units and abilities.
Leaders themselves and separate recruitable hero units will be able to gain experience and level up, while also being able to gain new equipment and powers. Players can also develop their alignment between good and evil based on their player's actions and the cultures the player absorbs into their empire, rather than race like the previous games in the series.
Cities themselves provide much of the resources, infrastructure and host to unit recruitment. Independent cities and units not immediately aligned to any player/leader are also present in the world map. Units that come from an unaffiliated city will fight to protect a city's domain, and they won't forget that they're tied to it. Many of these independent settlements aren't cities in the traditional sense, but can be alternative settlements, like a ""Giant's Keep"" for example. The player can conquer these holdings, which will provide units like a city, or they can absorb them through diplomatic means by paying tribute and diplomatic and/or alignment standing. Quests can also be given to players by independent forces and cities, including but not limited to clearing out wild units, searching for relics and even conquering cities and other holdings. Quests can grant the support of independent forces for player in addition to a reward such as gold or equipment, sometimes with the choice of either given to the player upon completion of the quest.
As in the case of the first game in the series, Age of Wonders III offers a story-driven campaign that is playable from two sides, the human-centric Commonwealth Empire and the Court of the High Elves. In addition to the campaign; single-player scenarios, online multiplayer, random map generation and a map editor are also available.[3] The graphics of Age of Wonders III will be presented in 3D instead of the isometric view the series has utilized up to this point.";Role-playing (RPG), Strategy, Tactical;;https://video.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_trailers/226840/15582/492ac761df2e9b0535ceda21a5f312188b2660b5/1750482434/hls_264_master.m3u8?t=1447359645;steam_226840;steam_226840;gog_1207660893;kartridge_226840;amazon_226840;gg_226840;gmg_226840;humble_ageofwonders3_bundle_steam;totalwar_ageofwonders3_bundle_steam;d2d_ageofwonders3_bundle_steam;humble_ageofwonders3_collection_steam;humble_ageofwonders3_steam;humble_ageofwonders3_fightforjustice_steam;steam_steam_226840;test_226840;test_age-of-wonders-iii;playfire_age-of-wonders-iii;test_steam_ageofwondersiii;test_gfn_226840;test_gfn_100350211;test_steam_226840;test_100350211;generic_51141403177294971;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
