2003 - UFO Aftermath;UFO Aftermath;UFO Aftermath;\\madhdd02\Software\GAMES\GAMES COMPIL\XCOM\2003 - UFO Aftermath;;OK;images\2003 - UFO Aftermath.jpg;2003;Warez;ALTAR Games;Cenega / Tri Synergy Inc.;03/10/2003;UFO: Aftermath is the first in a three-game squad-based tactical strategy-RPG series clearly inspired by the original X-COM games, with similar themes and gameplay, but with its own post-apocalyptic horror spin on the concept. The game is rendered in isometric 3D.;Strategy, Turn-based strategy (TBS), Tactical;XCOM;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XX3tfhS1eCI;igdb_8928;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
2005 - UFO Aftershock;UFO Aftershock;UFO Aftershock;\\madhdd02\Software\GAMES\GAMES COMPIL\XCOM\2005 - UFO Aftershock;;OK;images\2005 - UFO Aftershock.jpg;2005;Warez;ALTAR Games;Fulqrum Publishing;21/10/2005;"UFO: Aftershock is the second in a three-game squad-based tactical strategy-RPG series clearly inspired by the original X-COM games, with similar themes and gameplay, but with its own post-apocalyptic horror spin on the concept. The game is rendered in isometric 3D and, unlike its turn-based predecessor, features tactical combat in real-time with pause.

It is the year 2054. Fifty years after the disaster. Fifty years after the surface of Earth became uninhabitable. Retreating to the flying haven of the Laputa the remnants of humankind clung onto existence. Then a revolt against the increasingly rigid and corrupt human leadership of the Laputa escalated into a conflict that destroyed the colony. Now, the remaining survivors flee once again. Can they reclaim the Earth from the unknown forces that chased them into the skies?";Real Time Strategy (RTS), Role-playing (RPG), Strategy, Tactical;XCOM;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SZ13KRVktjQ;igdb_9853;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
2007 - UFO Afterlight;UFO Afterlight;UFO Afterlight;\\madhdd02\Software\GAMES\GAMES COMPIL\XCOM\2007 - UFO Afterlight;;OK;images\2007 - UFO Afterlight.jpg;2007;Warez;ALTAR Games;Bohemia Interactive, TopWare Interactive;01/12/2006;"UFO: Afterlight is the third in a three-game squad-based tactical strategy-RPG series clearly inspired by the original X-COM games, with similar themes and gameplay, but with its own post-apocalyptic horror spin on the concept. The game is rendered in isometric 3D and features tactical combat in real-time with pause.

UFO: Afterlight takes us to Mars, where a human colony has been built with the help of the Reticulans not long before the events of UFO: Aftershock took place.

The Martian base is self-sustainable and provides all the necessities for the survival of humans on a foreign planet, mainly breathable air, water and food. Although the people inhabiting this colony have the technologies and knowledge required for their further development, basic survival is their major concern. Their only activity is research of a nearby excavation site, which proves the existence of an ancient, intelligent and highly developed alien civilization.";Real Time Strategy (RTS), Role-playing (RPG), Strategy, Tactical;XCOM;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mcg3audA8Lg;igdb_16528;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
2007 - UFO Extraterrestrials;UFO Extraterrestrials;UFO Extraterrestrials;\\madhdd02\Software\GAMES\GAMES COMPIL\XCOM\2007 - UFO Extraterrestrials;;OK;images\2007 - UFO Extraterrestrials.jpg;2007;Warez;Chaos Concept;Tri Synergy;04/05/2007;UFO: Extraterrestrials is a Microsoft Windows game aimed to be a spiritual sequel to the highly acclaimed UFO: Enemy Unknown (retitled X-COM: UFO Defense in North America). Developed by Chaos Concept, the game incorporates a twist of the aliens defeating the humans on Earth. The game takes place on a human-colonized planet named Esperanza, where the alien threat has just arrived.;Strategy;XCOM;;igdb_9437;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
